Pune is the second-largest city in Maharashtra, India, after Mumbai. It's located on the western edge of the Deccan Plateau, on the leeward side of the Sahyadri Mountains.
Pune is known as the "Oxford of the East" due to its highly regarded educational institutions. It's also one of the largest IT hubs in India, and an important automobile and manufacturing hub. Pune has been ranked "the most liveable city in India" several times. 
Pune is also known as the "Queen of the Deccan" for its Maratha heritage and culture. It was once the center of power for the Maratha Empire, and is known to have existed as a town since 847 AD. Pune's rich historical past has made it the cultural capital of Maharashtra. 
Pune is surrounded by many forts and waterfalls. The city's moderate weather and rich flora and fauna make it an ideal travel destination. 
Pune's major languages are Marathi, Hindi, and English, but all Indian languages are spoken. Auto rickshaws, municipal and private buses, rental cars, and bicycles are available. 
